27/12/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Seventeen people reportedly were detained earlier this week in connection with a corruption case involving public procurement tenders. 
According to local media reports Tuesday (December 26th), the Ankara prosecutor's office ordered the detentions, saying that a total of 46 people were being investigated, including state officials. 
One case reportedly involves embezzlement and bribery in procurement procedures of the Turkish armed forces. 
(NTV - 26/12/06)
